        public static final AntAction.AntActionType DROP
        DROP action requires setting the fields: direction and quantity.

        When set by the client, if quantity exceeds the amount of food/water the ant is carrying, the command partly fails and the ant drops all its food in the specified cell.
        When set by the server, quantity is the number of units actually dropped by the ant on and preceding tick.

        The PICKUP action requires in one tick. However, during a given tick, ant actions of a nest are executed in the order the client places them in the list. Therefore, if two ants are are separated by an empty cell, then during a single tick, one ant can DROP food in the empty cell and the other can pick it up. This is a very efficient method of transporting a heavy load of food up hill, moving the food in one tick what would have taken a single ant 16 ticks to carry.
